description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a self-motivated, enthusiastic and committed band 5 Nurse to work as a Triage Nurse in the Award Winning E&amp;N Referral Hub based in Robertson House, Stevenage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following the rapid expansion of the Referral Hub the successful nurse will work alongside the Referral Hub GP&#39;s to provide expert clinical triage of nursing referrals into our services such as our POA service. The role includes telephone triaging patients to establish clinical needs and direct patients to the appropriate locality team or service. You will also be providing expert nursing advice, support and information to patients and colleagues on social prescribing and self-management as well as signposting to other services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Referral Hub is now able to triage via video consultations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be part of an energetic, patient focused team triaging patients for community nursing while working collaboratively with GPs, Acute hospitals, Social Care, Hospices and other third sector organisations. You will have the ability to make quick decisions with a high level of communications skills and be able to identify key early warning signs. You will work closely with the Clinical Manager in the hub and have opportunity to triage patients with a wide range of clinical presentations referred into our services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Referral Hub is open 8.00am – 8.00pm, the successful candidate will be required to join our triage rota covering these hours. Weekend working will also feature.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place on 30th November, 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tina Goddard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Triage Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: tina.goddard1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0300 123 7571&lt;/p&gt;
